criteria.textblock:
        Inclusion Criteria.

        To be eligible, participants should have unilateral rotator cuff tendinopathy and to
        present one positive finding in each of the following categories:

          -  Painful arc of movement during flexion or abduction;

          -  Neer (sensitivity 0.78, specificity 0.58) or Kennedy-Hawkins impingement signs
             (sensitivity 0.74, specificity 0.57);

          -  Pain on resisted external rotation, abduction or empty can test (sensitivity 0.69,
             specificity 0.62).

        Exclusion Criteria.

        Patients will be excluded if they have:

          -  an open wound that compromises KT application;

          -  had a previous shoulder surgery;

          -  allergy or intolerance to KT;

          -  adhesive capsulitis, defined as loss of passive shoulder ROM greater than 50%;

          -  history of glenohumeral luxation or fracture to the shoulder girdle;

          -  shoulder pain reproduced by cervical movements;

          -  clinical signs of full-thickness RC tears identified by lag signs tests (drop,
             internal, and external rotation signs).
